==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unliquored
<hw>Unliquored</hw> <def>See <er>liquored</er>.</def>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unliquored
<hw>Un*liq"uored</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
moistened or wet with liquor; dry.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Unliquored</xex>
coach.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not in liquor; not intoxicated; sober.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like an <qex>unliquored</qex> Silenus.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unlive</ent>⟦br⟧
